article.headline: Louisiana-Lafayette 68, Lamar 60
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Randell Daigle scored 19 points Saturday night to lead Louisiana-Lafayette to a 68-60 victory over Lamar. Chris Gradnigo scored 16 and Colby Batiste 12 for the Ragin' Cajuns (4-5). Tyren Johnson had seven points, seven rebounds and seven assists for Louisiana-Lafayette. Anthony Miles scored 14 to lead the Cardinals (4-7). Charlie Harper had 11 points and eight rebounds, and Justin Nabors 10 points and nine boards for Lamar. Louisiana-Lafayette outscored Lamar 34-30 in each half. The Ragin' Cajuns shot 43 percent from the field in each half while the Cardinals were 38 percent both before and after halftime.
